  <span id="freeText15675612424959293417" style="display:none">It would be wonderful if our entire country could get along like the people in this book. You have to have people who believe that all men are really created equal. This community was not far from our home and it is non-fiction. It is too bad that even after the Civil War when African Americans fought on the side of the North, they were still lynched and discriminated against in the North as well as the South. The book was interesting but I had a little trouble keeping everyone straight. It seemed to jump around quite a bit. Perhaps the author could have stayed with one family before going on to another.</span>
